%Y***********************************************************************       
%BCopyright%Y2025 Remarkable                                                    
%Y                                                                              
%YAll%Ycommands start with a dot (.)                                            
%YAll%Yvariable names you want to use start with the at sign (@)                
%YAll%Yfield definitions and colors will start with percent sign (%)            
%Y  For example %?G%G will start an unprotected GREEN colored field             
%Y  For example %?t%T will start a protected TURQOISE colored field             
%Y                                                                              
%Y*    Comment lines                                                            
%Y @<variable> is a variable name for example: @input                           
%Y                                                                              
%Y .F   Syntax: .F <location> <pfkno color> <prktxt color>                      
%Y        <keyno:assignment:label                                               
%Y      defines function keys for example:                                      
%Y       .F top %W %B 1:Help 3270:Help 3:QQUIT:Quit 12:FILE:Save                
%Y      location: can be TOP,BOT or a LINENnr                                   
%Y      colors are taken from 3270 CTLCHARS                                     
%Y      undefined keys will the disabled                                        
%Y                                                                              
%Y .Sn  Space n lines, if n is not specified it will be set to 1                
%Y                                                                              
%Y .C   Put the cursor on this location, row column                             
%Y                                                                              
%Y .I   Will imbed a file with definitions, fn ft fm, 1 level supported         
%Y                                                                              
%Y .D   Secondary input, fn ft fm, will be stored in @input.                    
%Y                                                                              
%Y .R   Read one or more lines from secondary input, fn ft fm (@input.)         
%Y                                                                              
%Y .W   Write all variables to a file, fn ft fm                                 
%Y                                                                              
%Y .X   Send all input fields/variables to Caller, all variable-names start     
%Y    with @-sign                                                               
%Y                                                                              
%Y*****************************************************************             
%Y                                                                              
%Y*                                                                             
%Y* Set ctlchars, attributes and colors                                         
%Y* For details see: HELP XEDIT SET                                             
%Y*                                                                             
SET CTLCHAR % ESCAPE                                                            
SET CTLCHAR Y PROTECT   YELLOW HIGH                                             
SET CTLCHAR y NOPROTECT YELLOW HIGH                                             
SET CTLCHAR W PROTECT   WHITE  HIGH                                             
SET CTLCHAR w NOPROTECT WHITE  HIGH                                             
SET CTLCHAR B PROTECT   BLUE   HIGH                                             
SET CTLCHAR b NOPROTECT BLUE   HIGH                                             
SET CTLCHAR G PROTECT   GREEN  HIGH                                             
SET CTLCHAR g NOPROTECT GREEN  HIGH                                             
SET CTLCHAR $ OFF                                                               
